## 1. Optimized Locking

* Reduces lock contention by using lightweight locking mechanisms.
* Improves concurrency for high-transaction workloads.
* Minimizes blocking between read and write operations.
* Uses Transaction ID (TID) based locking internally.
* Enhances performance for OLTP systems.
* Works efficiently with row versioning features.

---

## 2. TempDB Resource Governance

* Controls TempDB usage per workload or session.
* Prevents a single query from consuming all TempDB resources.
* Improves overall system stability under heavy load.
* Enables fair allocation of TempDB space.
* Reduces TempDB contention issues.
* Useful for multi-tenant or mixed workloads.

---

## 3. Optional Parameter Plan Optimization

* Improves execution plans for optional parameters in queries.
* Avoids inefficient plans caused by parameter sniffing.
* Generates multiple optimized plans based on input values.
* Enhances query performance for dynamic filters.
* Reduces need for manual query tuning.
* Works automatically without code changes.

---

## 4. Accelerated Database Recovery (ADR) for TempDB

* Speeds up recovery of TempDB after restart.
* Reduces rollback time for long-running transactions.
* Improves database availability.
* Uses version store for faster undo operations.
* Minimizes impact of transaction failures.
* Enhances overall system resilience.

---

## 5. Memory Optimized Container and Filegroup Removal

* Allows removal of unused memory-optimized filegroups.
* Simplifies database maintenance and cleanup.
* Frees up storage space efficiently.
* Reduces complexity in database structure.
* Supports better lifecycle management of in-memory objects.
* Helps in managing deprecated or unused features.

---

## 6. Optimized sp_executesql

* Improves execution performance of dynamic SQL queries.
* Enhances plan reuse for repeated executions.
* Reduces compilation overhead.
* Provides better parameter handling.
* Improves efficiency in high-frequency query execution.
* Useful for dynamic and parameterized workloads.

